==English==
===Etymology===
Shortening of plink-plonk , of uncertain origin: possibly an alteration of French vin blanc “white wine”.

Or possibly from the sound of wine being poured into a glass.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒŋk|-ɒŋk]]

===Noun===
'''plonk'''
#(''mostly British and Australian, informal'') [[cheap]] or [[inferior]] [[everyday]] [[wine]]
# the [[sound]] of something, especially [[liquid]], [[dropping]]
===Verb===
'''to plonk'''
# {{slang}} to set something down carelessly
#:''When you've finished with the sponge, just plonk it back in the sink.''
